aktisches Wissen und die Struktur von Handlungen; Wissen und das Problem des Dualismus; Disjunktivismus bezüglich Erfahrung und Wahrnehmung.  aThis volume contains contributions to the “systematic study of knowledge.” They suggest both an extension and a new path for classical epistemology. The topics in the second volume are the following: variants of skepticism; knowledge of the first, second, and third person; practical knowledge and the structure of action; knowledge and the problem of dualism; and disjunctivism concerning experience and perception.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aErkenntnistheorie. 4aSkeptizismus. 4aWissensformen. 4aWissensforschung. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh  aEpistemology.  aKnowledge Research.  aSkepticism.  aTypes of Knowledge.1 aAbel, Günter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBoyle, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassam, Quassim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConant, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConant, James, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDoyle, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinkelstein, David H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGustafsson, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaase, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaddock, Adrian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLockhart, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDowell, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcMyler, Benjamin, e